**Operating system or device - Godot version:**
Ubuntu 16.04 LTS - v2.1

**Issue description** (what happened, and what was expected):
Input event (_input(event)) is not emitted when mouse position is within a control node.

**Steps to reproduce:**
Make a control node, set the size & position to whatever you want.
Give it a script,

```
func _ready():
    set_process_input(true);

func _input(ie):
    if ie.type == InputEvent.MOUSE_BUTTON:
        print("Mouse button");

    if ie.type == InputEvent.MOUSE_MOTION:
        print("Mouse motion");
```

Play, and see the result.

**Link to minimal example project** (optional but very welcome):
https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B4y9gkD37fATSVJFbGV0anQ4c0k

Compiling godot 2.0.3 for openSUSE Linux (x86_64) will exit with an error that some functions return random data.
This happens due to the fact that there are some non-void functions without return or default return (if but no else).

Functions:

```
canvas_item.cpp new/scene/2d/canvas_item.cpp:
   bool CanvasItemMaterial::_set(const StringName& p_name, const Variant& p_value)

tools/editor/plugins/canvas_item_editor_plugin.cpp:
   bool CanvasItemEditor::_select(CanvasItem *item, Point2 p_click_pos, bool p_append, bool p_drag)
```

Here is a simple Patch:

`````` diff
diff -Nur godot-2.0.3-stable/scene/2d/canvas_item.cpp new/scene/2d/canvas_item.cpp
--- godot-2.0.3-stable/scene/2d/canvas_item.cpp 2016-05-13 08:06:31.000000000 +0200
+++ new/scene/2d/canvas_item.cpp        2016-06-27 01:50:56.733625313 +0200
@@ -37,6 +37,8 @@
 #include "scene/resources/style_box.h"
 #include "os/input.h"

+#include <cassert>
+
 bool CanvasItemMaterial::_set(const StringName& p_name, const Variant& p_value) {

        if (p_name==SceneStringNames::get_singleton()->shader_shader) {
@@ -391,6 +393,8 @@
                return last_valid->canvas_layer->get_transform() * xform;
        else if (is_inside_tree())
                return get_viewport()->get_canvas_transform() * xform;
+       assert(false && "Error this should never be reached");
+       return xform;
 }

 Matrix32 CanvasItem::get_global_transform() const {
diff -Nur godot-2.0.3-stable/tools/editor/plugins/canvas_item_editor_plugin.cpp new/tools/editor/plugins/canvas_item_editor_plugin.cpp
--- godot-2.0.3-stable/tools/editor/plugins/canvas_item_editor_plugin.cpp       2016-05-13 08:06:31.000000000 +0200
+++ new/tools/editor/plugins/canvas_item_editor_plugin.cpp      2016-06-27 01:48:40.164660129 +0200
@@ -634,6 +634,7 @@
                return true;

        }
+       return false;
 }

 void CanvasItemEditor::_key_move(const Vector2& p_dir, bool p_snap, KeyMoveMODE p_move_mode) {```
``````

Fix #5384.

@akien-mga sorry about the other PR, I should've tested more thoroughly, but didn't know about this vertical split special case.

@reduz, now I tested with and without the vertical split, and it worked fine. Changing minimum size to `Size2(0,150)` also solved the problem, but I think this is a better way to address the issue, as if anyone should change the minimum size again in the future, it won't cause a regression.

Any other special cases you may find useful for me to test before merging?
